CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_IS_FIXED
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Entity is Fixed/will not interact with Dynamic objects. Enables a indestructibility for archetype, making it static for props.

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_TOUGHFORBULLETS
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: This flag is used in instanced archetypes, used in instancedData in #map files.

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_HAS_ANIM
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: This flag is used in archetypes with bones inside models (YCD).

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_HAS_UVANIM
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: This flag is used in archetypes with UV animations (YCD).

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_SHADOW_ONLY
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Blocks lights and shadows and does not render the model. [Credits to DPS] Note from DPS: I will have to do more research in depth for that to be sure.

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_DONT_CAST_SHADOWS
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Object will not cast Shadows (Used with overlays/decals). [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_IS_TYPE_OBJECT
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: This flag enables a destructibility for archetype, making it dynamic for props. Needed for GET_CLOSEST_OBJECT_OF_TYPE native and other OBJECT related natives like CREATE_OBJECT.

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_AUTOSTART_ANIM
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Allows to play ycd animations on dynamic objects. Only available for objects with flag FLAG_IS_TYPE_OBJECT

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_DOOR_PHYSICS
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Enables special attribute for door archetypes. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_DONT_AVOID_BY_PEDS
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Disable red vertex channel for object. [Credits to DPS]

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_USE_AMBIENT_SCALE
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Disable green vertex channel for object. Props commonly use this. Makes archetypes with white vertexes dont glow at night. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_IS_DEBUG
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Disable blue vertex channel for object. [Credits to DPS]

CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.name: FLAG_HAS_ALPHA_SHADOW
CBaseArchetypeDefFlags.description: Disable Alpha vertex channel for object. [Credits to DPS]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_SLIDE_LEFTRIGHT_ON_APPROACH_1
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_SLIDE_LEFTRIGHT_ON_APPROACH_2
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _ENABLE_TRAFFIC_GYR_LIGHTS
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Traffic lights use this - Enables the GYR Lights. [Credits to Carl Johnson] Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_SLIDE_LEFTRIGHT_ON_APPROACH_3
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_MOVE_UPDOWN
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Up/down 90 degrees (garage doors). [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_SLIDE_LEFTRIGHT_ON_APPROACH_4
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_PUSH_BY_ENTITY
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Pushed by player/ped/vehicle. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_SLIDE_LEFTRIGHT_ON_APPROACH_5
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_MOVE_LEFT_ON_CONTACT_1
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Doors move in contact with player in 90 degrees to left. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_MOVE_UPDOWN_ON_APPROACH
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Vertical auto move in straight line up/down when player aproach. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _PROC_OBJECT
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: CEntityDef Proc Plants/weeds/bushes use this. [Credits to Carl Johnson] Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach, doors collision dont work. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_MOVE_LEFT_ON_CONTACT_2
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Doors move in contact with player in 90 degrees to left. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _DOOR_SLIDE_LEFTRIGHT_ON_APPROACH
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Specify how doors will be open - Slides left <-> right when player aproach, doors collision dont work. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.name: _TREE_SHADOWSPROXY
CBaseArchetypeDefSpecialAttributeFlags.description: Trees that uses shadow proxy. [Credits to Dekurwinator]

CTimeArchetypeDefTimeFlags.name: _SETUP_TIME
CTimeArchetypeDefTimeFlags.description: This flag needs to be set with every other time flag, otherwise it will not work. Credits to Dekurwinator

CMloArchetypeDefCEntityDefFlags.name: FLAG_IS_FIXED
CMloArchetypeDefCEntityDefFlags.description: Static entity. Fixed/will not interact with Dynamic objects. [Credits to dexyfex]

CMloArchetypeDefCEntityDefFlags.name: FLAG_ONLY_RENDER_IN_SHADOWS
CMloArchetypeDefCEntityDefFlags.description: Object won't stream (or be invisible). [Credits to Carl Johnson]

CMloArchetypeDefCEntityDefFlags.name: FLAG_DONT_RENDER_IN_REFLECTIONS
CMloArchetypeDefCEntityDefFlags.description: Object will not cast reflections. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.name: ROOM_FREEZEPEDS
CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.description: Controls whether if shooting a gun in a interior will or will not alert the police. It would have something to do with sound from inside to MLO is heard outside. Should be used in homes or private property, but only in rooms that are private like bedrooms, bathrooms and not in common or open rooms like living, dinning and kitchens. Example enabled: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PV2hZy2oZYg Example disabled: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DGUQBz9lJ88

CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.name: ROOM_NO_DIR_LIGHT
CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.description: Disables Interior shadowcasting in exterior. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.name: ROOM_REDUCE_CARS
CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.description: Reduces vehicle population creating by 66% (applies 0.33 modifier) when player is in this room. [Credits to Disquse]

CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.name: ROOM_REDUCE_PEDS
CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.description: Reduces peds population creating by 66% (applies 0.33 modifier) when player is in this room. [Credits to Disquse]

CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.name: ROOM_DONT_RENDER_EXTERIOR
CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.description: Disables all limbo portals. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.name: ROOM_MIRROR_POTENTIALLY_VISIBLE
CMloArchetypeDefRoomFlags.description: Used in rooms with mirrors. [Credits to Disquse] Note from DPS: Game will hardcode this flag into rooms with mirrors anyway, so this flag is useless.

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_ONE_WAY
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: You can see from the interior to the exterior, but not vice versa. Used for windows in interiors such as the ammunation in Vinewood. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_LINK
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: You can see from the exterior into the interior, but not vice versa. Used for connecting two MLOs together, such as V_MICHAEL and V_MICHAEL_GARAGE. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_MIRROR
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Mirror. No direct entrance? [Credits to dexyfex]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_IGNORE_MODIFIER
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Portal will render the outside with much more bloom. Generaly windows use this. Will not only make a portal appear with more bloom but will also make the player NOT glow when you are near the portal (so a portal to limbo room without flag 8 will cause a player to glow when near)

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_LOWLODONLY
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Renders limbo as LOD. Used in the roof window of V_MICHAEL. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_ALLOWCLOSING
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Disable portal while a door is closed as an attached entity. Note that Rockstar frequently uses this portal, even when there are not any attached entities. May have other functions. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_MIRROR_USING_PORTAL_TRAVERSAL
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Enables limbo portals in mirror portal reflections, but does not enable limbo entities. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_MIRROR_CAN_SEE_EXTERIOR_VIEW
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Renders limbo entities in portal reflections. [Credits to DPS]

CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.name: INTINFO_PORTAL_USE_LIGHT_BLEED
CMloArchetypeDefPortalFlags.description: Tells the portal to blend the timecycle with the outside world so when the player is near the portal, the room time cycle is blended with the outside world. Makes see through glass doors? Interior timecycle farclipping gets ignored and the entire world distance is rendered.

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _INTERACTIVE_PROP
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Seems to be used on destructable/interactive props - props that are of this type will fall through the map/interior if this flag is not enabled. [Credits to Carl Johnson]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _INTERACTIVE_PROP_TREE
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Seems to be used on non destructable/intercative props like trees. [Credits to Carl Johnson]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _LOD
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Seems to used on LODs. [Credits to Carl Johnson]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: STATIC
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Static entity - Entity is Invincible/will not interact with dymaic Dynamic. [Credits to dexyfex]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _DONT_GET_DARK
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Object does not get dark at night time? [Credits to Mellowtri]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: DISABLE_EMBEDDED_LIGHTSOURCE
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Disable embedded light source. [Credits to Mellowtri]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _ALWAYS_ON_1
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Seems to be used on almost everything - should be used by default. [Credits to Carl Johnson]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _ALWAYS_ON_2
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Seems to be used on almost everything - should be used by default. [Credits to Carl Johnson]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: DONT_CAST_SHADOWS
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Object will not cast shadows. [Credits to Mellowtri]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: DONT_RENDER
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Object will not render but still cast shadows. [Credits to Mellowtri and Carl Johnson]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: DONT_CAST_REFLECTIONS
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Object will not cast reflections. [Credits to DPS]

FwEntityDefFlags.name: _LOD_UNK
FwEntityDefFlags.description: Seems to be LODs related. [Credits to Mellowtri]

CCarGenFlags.name: FLAG_HIGHPRIORITY
CCarGenFlags.description: Seems to make the cargen almost-always spawn. [Credits to Monky]

CCarGenFlags.name: FLAG_POLICE
CCarGenFlags.description: Spawns police police2 police3 policeb or sherrif.

CCarGenFlags.name: _IS_LARGE_VEHICLE
CCarGenFlags.description: Commonly used on bigger parking spots together with the flag 1073741824

CCarGenFlags.name: _IS_LARGE_VEHICLE_2
CCarGenFlags.description: Commonly used on bigger parking spots together with the flag 536870912

CCarGenFlags.name: _IS_WATER_VEHICLE
CCarGenFlags.description: Mostly used on car generators in the water

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: CAST_SHADOWS_FOR_OBJECTS
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Objects that do not move will have shadows casted. Excludes moving parts such as players, moving props and vehicles.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: CAST_SHADOWS_FOR_ENTITIES
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Objects that move will cast shadows. Includes moving parts such as player, moving props and vehicles.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: FAKE_SUN_LIGHT
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Will turn light into a so-called sunlight. The light will change its color and intensity depending on the time of day. Will disable when there is no sun light. Color and intensity is primary affected by factors such as time, weather and light property intensity.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: ENABLE_ELECTRICAL_HUM_01
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Electrical Hum [1]. Light will produce an audible hum.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: ENABLE_ELECTRICAL_HUM_02
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Electrical Hum [2] (Audio hum). Light will produce an audible hum.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: ENABLE_LIGHT_VOLUME
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Lights will have a volumetric cone casted. Use the 'Light Volume' section in GIMS Evo to control this.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: DISABLE_SPECULARITY
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Light will not cast reflections on materials. Light will not affect specular properties in the environment. Will turn light into a so-called 'fill light'

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: DISABLE
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Disables the light. Purpose unknown. Perhaps there is a trigger that will activate the light under some condition.

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: DISABLE_FOR_MIRROR_PORTALS
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Deactivates the light in a mirror portal. [Credits to Gusepe73]

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: INVISIBLE_CORONA
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Invisible corona (can be visible in menu only).

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: ENABLE_CULLING_PLANE
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Enable culling plane, stopping the light from casting after some value x,y,z normal plane followed by distance; x=1, y=2, z=3, distance =4 (1,2,3,4) [x,y,z,d]. [Credits to DPS]

DrawableLightAttributesFlags.name: _DONT_CAST_LIGHT_ON_GLASS
DrawableLightAttributesFlags.description: Don't cast light onto glass material (tentative for exact function however this is the first thing i noticed)

IMapFlags.name: SCRIPTABLE
IMapFlags.description: This flag forces file to be enabled/disabled by REQUEST_IPL native.

IMapFlags.name: DETERMINE_LOD_OBJECT_ARRAY
IMapFlags.description: This flag is set to determine LOD objects in entities array.

IMapContentFlags.name: CONTENTFLAG_MASK_LODS
IMapContentFlags.description: This map contains LOD entities type, as SLOD2 and higher.

IMapContentFlags.name: CONTENTFLAG_BLOCKINFO
IMapContentFlags.description: This map contains SLOD1 entities type.

IMapContentFlags.name: CONTENTFLAG_DISTANT_LOD_LIGHTS
IMapContentFlags.description: This map contains distant LOD lights.

IMapContentFlags.name: CONTENTFLAG_ENTITIES_CRITICAL
IMapContentFlags.description: This map is ‘critical’ and should be placed in the ‘critical’ box streamer slot. Used for maps with tall objects such as lamp posts and trees.

IMapContentFlags.name: CONTENTFLAG_INSTANCE_LIST
IMapContentFlags.description: This map contains grass instances from instancedData in fwMapData.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_LOOPING
AnimationFlags.description: Keep repeating animation.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_HOLD_LAST_FRAME
AnimationFlags.description: Stop animation at the last animation frame.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_REPOSITION_WHEN_FINISHED
AnimationFlags.description: Matches the peds physical representation position with the visual representation position after the animation ended.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_NOT_INTERRUPTABLE
AnimationFlags.description: Animation can't be interrupted by external events.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_UPPERBODY
AnimationFlags.description: Only animate upper body of ped model.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_SECONDARY
AnimationFlags.description: Animation runs in the secondary task slot which enables the player to for example move.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_REORIENT_WHEN_FINISHED
AnimationFlags.description: Matches the peds physical representation direction with the visual representation direction after the animation ended.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_ABORT_ON_PED_MOVEMENT
AnimationFlags.description: Ends the animation as soon as the ped tries to move.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_ADDITIVE
AnimationFlags.description: Playback the animation additively. Only works with special animations.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_TURN_OFF_COLLISION
AnimationFlags.description: Disables collision direction while animation is playing.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_OVERRIDE_PHYSICS
AnimationFlags.description: Do not apply any physic forces while animation is playing. Also turns off collision

AnimationFlags.name: AF_IGNORE_GRAVITY
AnimationFlags.description: Do not apply gravity while animation is playing.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_EXTRACT_INITIAL_OFFSET
AnimationFlags.description: Extracts the initial offset of the playback position. To be used when playing synced animations on different peds.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_EXIT_AFTER_INTERRUPTED
AnimationFlags.description: Exits the animation after getting interrupted by a different task (e.g. Natural Motion)

AnimationFlags.name: AF_TAG_SYNC_IN
AnimationFlags.description: Sync the animation whilst blending in

AnimationFlags.name: AF_TAG_SYNC_OUT
AnimationFlags.description: Sync the animation whilst blending out.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_TAG_SYNC_CONTINUOUS
AnimationFlags.description: Sync the animation all the time.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_FORCE_START
AnimationFlags.description: Force the animation to start even if the ped is falling, ragdolling, ...

AnimationFlags.name: AF_USE_KINEMATIC_PHYSICS
AnimationFlags.description: Use the kinematic physics mode on the entity for the duration of the animation.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_USE_MOVER_EXTRACTION
AnimationFlags.description: Updates the peds capsule position every frame based on the animation. Used with USE_KINEMATIC_PHYSICS.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_HIDE_WEAPON
AnimationFlags.description: Hides the weapon during animation.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_ENDS_IN_DEAD_POSE
AnimationFlags.description: Kills the ped after the animation finished.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_ACTIVATE_RAGDOLL_ON_COLLISION
AnimationFlags.description: If the peds ragdoll makes contact with anything physical active ragdoll and fall over.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_DONT_EXIT_ON_DEATH
AnimationFlags.description: Prevents secondary animation task to end on death.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_ABORT_ON_WEAPON_DAMAGE
AnimationFlags.description: Cancels the animation on damage events. Also works if NOT_INTERRUPTABLE is set.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_DISABLE_FORCED_PHYSICS_UPDATE
AnimationFlags.description: Prevent adjusting the capsule on the enter state of the animation.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_PROCESS_ATTACHMENTS_ON_START
AnimationFlags.description: Forces the attachments to be processed at the start of the animation.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_EXPAND_PED_CAPSULE_FROM_SKELETON
AnimationFlags.description: Expands the capsule to the extents of the skeleton.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_USE_ALTERNATIVE_FP_ANIM
AnimationFlags.description: Plays an alternative version of the animation if the player is in first person mode.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_BLENDOUT_WRT_LAST_FRAME
AnimationFlags.description: Starts blending out the animation earlier, so that blend out duration finishes with the animation.

AnimationFlags.name: AF_USE_FULL_BLENDING
AnimationFlags.description: Use full blending for this anim and override the heading/position adjustment.
